quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  28,1,Ta Seen Meem
  28,2,these are the verses of the Book that make everything clear
  28,3,We recite to you from the story of Moses and Pharaoh setting out the Truth for people who believe
  28,4,"Pharaoh exalted himself and divided the people into factions: oppressing a segment of them, slaughtering their sons while sparing the women. He was one of those who spread corruption"
  28,5,"But, We wanted to favor those who were oppressed in the land, and make them leaders and make them inheritors of the land"
  28,6,"and to empower them and show Pharaoh, Haman and their soldiers through them the very thing that they feared"
  28,7,"So, We inspired Moses' mother, \"Nurse him for now; but when you fear for his safety, put him into the river; do not be afraid and do not grieve. We will return him to you and will make him a messenger"
  28,8,"And Pharaoh's people picked him up, to become later an enemy to them and a source of grief, [since] Pharaoh and Haman and their soldiers were sinners"
  28,9,"Pharaoh's wife said, \"He will be a delight for my eyes and yours. Do not kill him; He may be useful to us, or we may adopt him as a son.\" They did not realize [the consequences of] what was going on"
  28,10,"[Later] Moses' mother felt her heart totally empty. She was about to disclose the matter had We not strengthened her heart that she would be counted among the believers"
  28,11,"And she said to his sister, \"Follow him,\" so she watched him from a distance without being noticed"
  28,12,"And We made him reject all wet nurses, so she said, \"Shall I tell you about a household that will feed him for you and be good to him"
  28,13,"And We returned him to his mother so that she might delight her eyes with him, not grieve and know that God's promise is true. But most people do not know"